<p><b>Greater NY Health Organization</b> is helping to locate family members and accepting reports of missing persons.</p>
<ul>
<li>status of family members: <b>(212) 560-2730</b> 
<li>to report a missing person: <b>(212) 560-8029</b> 
</ul>

<p><b>The Pentagon</b> has published the following numbers for gaining information about family or friends: </p>
<ul>
<li>Army: <b>(800) 984-8523</b> 
<li>Air Force <b>(800) 253-9276</b> 
<li>Navy and Marines <b>(877) 663-6772</b>
</ul>

<p><b>The Red Cross</b> has asked that all inquiries regarding family members be directed to your local Red Cross chapter.  For Chicago call <b>(312) 729-6100</b></p>

<p>For more information about loved ones who may be injured or hospitalized in the New York area:
<ul>
<li>Go to the official New York City web site at <a href="http://www.home.nyc.gov" target="_blank">www.home.nyc.gov</a>
<li>Call New York City Disaster Relief:  <b>(212) 516-2730</b>
<li>Call the New York City Hotline:  <b>(800) 222-6459</b>
</ul>

